<main class="orgchart" id="orgchart-top">

  <header class="orgchart__intro">
    <p class="orgchart__intro-eyebrow">Government structure · El Paso County, Colorado</p>
    <h1>How government is organized here — and where to find the work</h1>
    <p>Federal sets the floor. State writes the rules. Local makes the day-to-day decisions about your address. Every box below is a real agency with real decision-making authority; every link inside a box opens a record, audit, dashboard, or form that lives on this site.</p>
    <p>If you're looking for something specific, the <a href="/#tier-local">Start Here</a> block on the homepage will route by ZIP. This page is for understanding the structure.</p>
  </header>

  <!-- ═══ FEDERAL TIER ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="orgchart__tier orgchart__tier--federal" id="orgchart-federal" aria-labelledby="orgchart-federal-title">
    <div class="orgchart__tier-band">
      <p class="orgchart__tier-eyebrow">Tier 3 · Federal &amp; private sector</p>
      <h2 class="orgchart__tier-title" id="orgchart-federal-title">Federal government &amp; private-sector accountability</h2>
      <p class="orgchart__tier-intro">The federal layer sets minimum standards (ADA Title II, antitrust, HUD funding) and operates national reporting infrastructure. Private-sector platforms appear here when their products are operated at federal scale and their accessibility or competition behavior affects residents nationwide.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="orgchart__grid" role="list">

      <article class="orgchart__card" role="listitem">
        <div class="orgchart__card-head">
          <h3 class="orgchart__card-name">U.S. Department of Justice — Civil Rights</h3>
          <span class="orgchart__card-tag orgchart__card-tag--active">Active</span>
        </div>
        <p class="orgchart__card-role">Enforces ADA Title II across local government websites and services. Filing path for accessibility complaints; co-plaintiff with state AGs on antitrust matters (RealPage).</p>
        <p class="orgchart__works-label">Work on this site</p>
        <ul class="orgchart__works">
          <li><a class="orgchart__work" href="/microsites/national/DOJ/doj-complaint-redesign.html">DOJ Civil Rights complaint — accessible redesign <span class="orgchart__work-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="orgchart__card" role="listitem">
        <div class="orgchart__card-head">
          <h3 class="orgchart__card-name">Federal Trade Commission (FTC)</h3>
          <span class="orgchart__card-tag orgchart__card-tag--active">Active</span>
        </div>
        <p class="orgchart__card-role">Consumer protection and fraud reporting; ReportFraud.ftc.gov is the national consumer-fraud complaint portal.</p>
        <p class="orgchart__works-label">Work on this site</p>
        <ul class="orgchart__works">
          <li><a class="orgchart__work" href="/microsites/national/FTC/ftc-reportfraud-ada-audit.html">ReportFraud.ftc.gov — WCAG 2.1 AA audit <span class="orgchart__work-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="orgchart__card" role="listitem">
        <div class="orgchart__card-head">
          <h3 class="orgchart__card-name">Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI)</h3>
          <span class="orgchart__card-tag orgchart__card-tag--active">Active</span>
        </div>
        <p class="orgchart__card-role">Federal law-enforcement intake — tip submission, IC3 cybercrime, public-records requests.</p>
        <p class="orgchart__works-label">Work on this site</p>
        <ul class="orgchart__works">
          <li><a class="orgchart__work" href="/microsites/FBI/tips-fbi-redesign.html">FBI tip-submission — redesign proposal <span class="orgchart__work-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="orgchart__card" role="listitem">
        <div class="orgchart__card-head">
          <h3 class="orgchart__card-name">U.S. Dept of Housing &amp; Urban Development (HUD)</h3>
          <span class="orgchart__card-tag orgchart__card-tag--active">Active</span>
        </div>
        <p class="orgchart__card-role">Funds local housing programs (HOME-ARP, CDBG). Requires public-comment processes under 24 CFR 91.105 — which is what drove the accessible HOME-ARP form rebuild.</p>
        <p class="orgchart__works-label">Work on this site</p>
        <ul class="orgchart__works">
          <li><a class="orgchart__work" href="/microsites/city/housing/housing-drupal-arp-formADA/home-arp-form-preview.html">HOME-ARP form — accessible HTML preview <span class="orgchart__work-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li>
          <li><a class="orgchart__work" href="/microsites/city/housing/housing-drupal-arp-formADA/bundle-readme.html">HOME-ARP bundle — Drupal Webform replacement <span class="orgchart__work-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li>
        </ul>
      </article>

